<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="65" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1435,514,607]" pageId="1" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,268,514,538]" pageId="1" pageNumber="65">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName box="[379,536,514,537]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Micrathena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cyanospina">
<emphasis box="[379,536,514,537]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="65">M. cyanospina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from those of other species in the 
<taxonomicName box="[1145,1235,514,537]" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Micrathena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="militaris">
<emphasis box="[1145,1235,514,537]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="65">militaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by the dark and uniform coloration (
<figureCitation box="[412,512,549,572]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 1 – 2" captionStart-1="FIGURES 3 – 5" captionStartId-0="1.[151,258,1563,1584]" captionStartId-1="2.[151,258,1905,1926]" captionTargetBox-0="[359,1228,658,1542]" captionTargetBox-1="[187,1395,319,1829]" captionTargetId-0="figure@1.[359,1228,658,1542]" captionTargetId-1="figure@2.[151,1436,263,1881]" captionTargetPageId-0="1" captionTargetPageId-1="2" captionText-0="FIGURES 1 – 2. Micrathena cyanospina, male from Pico da Neblina, São Gabriel da Cachoeira, Amazonas. 1. Dorsal. 2. Lateral." captionText-1="FIGURES 3 – 5. Micrathena cyanospina: 3. Male from Pico da Neblina, São Gabriel da Cachoeira, Amazonas, dorsal. 4 – 5. Male palp. 4. Mesal. 5. Lateral. Abbreviations: A, terminal apophysis; C, conductor; Cy, cymbium; E, embolus; M, median apophysis; P. paracymbium; T, tegulum. Scale bars: figure 3 - 1 mm, figures 4 and 5 - 0.5 mm." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/279113/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/279114/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="65">
Figs. 
<number box="[473,512,549,572]" pageId="1" pageNumber="65" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
</figureCitation>
) and by the pilose posterior area of the abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[1052,1155,549,572]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 1 – 2" captionStart-1="FIGURES 3 – 5" captionStartId-0="1.[151,258,1563,1584]" captionStartId-1="2.[151,258,1905,1926]" captionTargetBox-0="[359,1228,658,1542]" captionTargetBox-1="[187,1395,319,1829]" captionTargetId-0="figure@1.[359,1228,658,1542]" captionTargetId-1="figure@2.[151,1436,263,1881]" captionTargetPageId-0="1" captionTargetPageId-1="2" captionText-0="FIGURES 1 – 2. Micrathena cyanospina, male from Pico da Neblina, São Gabriel da Cachoeira, Amazonas. 1. Dorsal. 2. Lateral." captionText-1="FIGURES 3 – 5. Micrathena cyanospina: 3. Male from Pico da Neblina, São Gabriel da Cachoeira, Amazonas, dorsal. 4 – 5. Male palp. 4. Mesal. 5. Lateral. Abbreviations: A, terminal apophysis; C, conductor; Cy, cymbium; E, embolus; M, median apophysis; P. paracymbium; T, tegulum. Scale bars: figure 3 - 1 mm, figures 4 and 5 - 0.5 mm." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/279113/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/279114/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="65">
Figs. 
<number box="[1113,1155,549,572]" pageId="1" pageNumber="65" value="2.0" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.0">1–3</number>
</figureCitation>
). The palp has a large and truncated embolus on the top of bulb and a triangular median apophysis (
<figureCitation box="[930,996,584,607]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 5" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1905,1926]" captionTargetBox="[187,1395,319,1829]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,263,1881]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 5. Micrathena cyanospina: 3. Male from Pico da Neblina, São Gabriel da Cachoeira, Amazonas, dorsal. 4 – 5. Male palp. 4. Mesal. 5. Lateral. Abbreviations: A, terminal apophysis; C, conductor; Cy, cymbium; E, embolus; M, median apophysis; P. paracymbium; T, tegulum. Scale bars: figure 3 - 1 mm, figures 4 and 5 - 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279114/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="65">
Fig. 
<number box="[980,996,584,607]" pageId="1" pageNumber="65" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
